   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject Two Hundred Nine THE PLEASURES OF THE NEW JERUSALEM Scripture: Rev 21:10; 22:5; 7:15-17 The New Jerusalem is a shining city Rev 21:21, 18; 4:3 The street is pure gold signifying God s divine nature.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>The gates are pearls signifying our entrance into the city through Christ s redemption.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The wall is jasper signifying the riches of the divine life in the believers.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The New Jerusalem is God s dwelling place There is the throne of God and of the Lamb Rev 22:1 .</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>There is the glory of God shining through the Lord Jesus as the lamp Rev 21:23 .</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The New Jerusalem is full of the enjoyment of the blessing of life There is the tree of life Rev 22:2 .</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>There is the water of life Rev 22:1 .</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The New Jerusalem is where God s eternal care is manifested God s light will shine over it.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Christ will be shepherding there.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>In the New Jerusalem there is no more hunger, thirst, tears, darkness, or suffering There will be no hunger or thirst Rev 7:16 .</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>There will be no darkness Rev 22:5 .</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>There will be no tears Rev 21:4 .</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>There will be no suffering Rev 21:4 .</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>How to enter into the New Jerusalem Repent and believe in the Lord Jesus.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Through believing, your name will be written in the Lamb s book of life.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Only those whose names are written in the book of life can enter into the New Jerusalem Rev 21:27 .</S>
   </TEXT>
